# Treento API

REST API for urban green space management: tree/green space consultation, reporting, and adoption.
Authentication via JWT (Bearer Token).

## Authentication [/auth]

### Sign up [POST /auth/signup]
Creates a new user account.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Body
        {
            "email": "user1@test.com",
            "password": "Password123"
        }

+ Response 201

### Login [POST /auth/login]
Authenticates a user and returns a JWT token.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Body
        {
            "email": "user1@test.com",
            "password": "Password123"
        }

+ Response 200

## Trees [/trees]

### Get all trees [GET /trees]
Returns the list of trees available in the system.

+ Parameters
    + limit (optional, number) - Limits the number of returned trees

+ Response 200 (application/json)

## Reports [/reports]

### Create report [POST /reports]
Creates a new report. Authentication required.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers
        Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

    + Body
        {
            "title": "Broken tree",
            "location": "Via Roma"
        }

+ Response 201